Metasoma. First tergite 0.4 times as long as apically wide, gradually narrowed basally, flattened medially and weakly convex apically; 
second-fifth
tergites largely densely coarsely punctate and rather moderately shiny; second sternite similarly sculptured as tergite, its medio-apical protuberance lamelliform and convex medio-apically (Fig. 129) and with pair of triangular submedial teeth, third sternite only with distinct ledge (Fig. 129); hypopygium truncate apically.
